  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Graft-versus-host-disease (GVHD) is a major obstacle to successful allogeneic hematopoietic
      cell transplantation (alloHCT). Cannabidiol (CBD), a non-psychotropic ingredient of Cannabis
      sativa possesses potent anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties. In a recent phase
      2 study, CBD has been shown to be safe and reduced significantly the incidence of acute GVHD
      compared to control patients with a hazard ratio of 0.3. Based on these results the
      investigators propose a phase 2 study to explore the efficacy of oral CBD in the treatment of
      severe (grades III/IV) acute GVHD, a pathology with a dismal prognosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
